 Time Zones are a Drag … Seriously 
	 November 24, 2017 
	 by  SQLSoldier 
	 SQL Server 
	 1 Comment 
	 1 
 


 Time Zones  Time Zones were definitely being a drag today. I got an email from one of the developers at work asking about the performance difference between 2 queries. The only difference between the 2 queries is that one of them uses the  AT TIME ZONE  clause that was added in SQL Server 2016. I have not played around with this particular clause, but we do store quite a bit of data in the datetimeoffset data type. In the table in the developer’s queries, the data 